{
  "stem": "5758.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you can see-- I remember the faces of the people who surrounded him laughing, ha-ha, you know, dirty Jew and-- and-- and he-- he wore a hat.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And underneath the hat he wore a-- a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't know how you call it, a--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A kippah-- skull--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Kippah, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Skullcap, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the hat fell down, and they wanted to pick it up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They pick-- they-- they played football-- football with it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, one S-- SR-- it was the SR-- man in brown uniform with the swastika [INAUDIBLE], gave him a kick in-- in his face.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And blood was streaming down, and he had to go and continue cleaning.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[SIGHS] I will never, ever forget this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was so inhuman.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was really the first experience that I had of unjustified violence against a human being, from one human being to another one.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And since the time, my parents really said, well, only when you go to school-- not the-- the tailoring [INAUDIBLE], and I don't want you to go and-- and-- and go or out walking in the street, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] If I may come back a little bit on the-- when the German went-- entered, the troops entered.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was the 11th of March.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And before that, the night before, there were always anti-- anti-- anti-Nazi demonstration by the communists and by the socialists, because there was a very large contingent of-- of left-wing people.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they went-- in Vienna, the biggest street is the Ring.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there were always parades and red flags and-- and-- and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] thousands and thousands of people went there to-- and my brothers and I also joined.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
